      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The 2nd Amendment is a fundamental right, but the right to bear arms is not absolute, and its interpretation is subject to reasonable regulations. The Supreme Court has already established that certain restrictions, such as background checks and magazine capacity limits, are permissible under the 2nd Amendment. In fact, the Court's decision in District of Columbia v. Heller (2008) recognized that the right to bear arms is not unlimited and can be subject to reasonable regulations.",
